      <div class="modal-body">
        <p>The Backseat gives eloquent and critical writers a chance to write engaging stories about provoking and relevant topics to an equally curious audience.</p>
        <p>In other words, if you like writing and reading about dope shit, stick around.</p>
        <p><strong>Who is driving this vehicle?</strong></p>
        <p>Sara Grossman is our editor in chief.</p>
        <p>Michael Rosen is our editorial director.</p>
        <p>Anya Schultz is our creative director and senior editor.</p>
        <p>Michael Lannin is our online director.</p>
        <p>Kimberly Veklerov is our copy chief.</p>
        <p><strong>Where are you located?</strong></p>
        <p>Most likely on your iPhone or perhaps Chrome or Safari on your laptop. But if you’re really wondering, we’re on a server. Where, you ask? That’s a good question, someone should do a story on that.</p>
        <p><strong>No really, where are you located?</strong></p>
        <p>We’re based in the San Francisco Bay Area, but our contributors come from all over the country.</p>
        <p><strong>Why are you called the Backseat?</strong></p>
        <p>The front seat sounded too forward.</p>
        <p><strong>How can I contribute?</strong></p>
        <p>Pitch us! Email story ideas to <a href="mailto:thebackseatpitches@gmail.com">thebackseatpitches@gmail.com</a>. No idea is a bad idea, unless we say so. We think the most interesting things in the world are the things we know nothing about, so pitch us something ridiculous.</p>
        <p><strong>How much do you pay for stories?</strong></p>
        <p>Full disclosure: We aren’t paying anything right now. We are broke college kids. But perhaps our most pressing goal right now is to get to the point where we can pay our writers at least a little bit of money, and we plan on getting there quickly.</p>
        <p><strong>I take photos.</strong></p>
        <p>Nice.</p>
        <p><strong>Do you want them?</strong></p>
        <p>Yes, email <a href="mailto:thebackseatpitches@gmail.com">thebackseatpitches@gmail.com</a>.</p>
